# TypeScript & Component Conventions

## Types

- Props as `type Props = {}`, not `interface` (interfaces are for extendable contracts)
- No `any` ‚Äî ever. Model the type instead.
- Entity types in `types/` must mirror future API response shape ‚Äî no UI-only fields on them
- Messages types live in `types/` alongside their entity (e.g., `types/run.ts` has both `RunType` and `RunDetailMessages`)

## Component File Structure

```tsx
'use client';                    // 1. directive (only if needed)

import ...                      // 2. React ‚Üí Next ‚Üí 3rd party ‚Üí @/types ‚Üí @/utils ‚Üí @/components

type Props = { ... };           // 3. Props type

export default function MyComp({ prop1, prop2 }: Props) {
  // a. hooks (useState, useMemo, useEffect...)
  // b. derived values (useMemo for filtered lists, computed labels)
  // c. handlers (handleSubmit, handleDelete...)
  // d. early returns (null guards, loading)
  // e. JSX
}

function SubItem({ ... }: { ... }) { ... }   // 5. private sub-components (bottom of file)

const helper = (x: number) => x * 2;        // 6. pure helpers (no hooks, not exported)
```

## State

- `useState` for mutable state owned by the component
- `useMemo` for derived/filtered data ‚Äî never recompute in the render body
- `useEffect` for URL param reading only; never for state-to-state sync
- URL `searchParams` for tab selection and filter state (survives reload)

## Patterns

```tsx
// Optional chaining ‚Äî always
member?.User?.username

// Data access via hooks (not direct mockData imports)
const project = useProject(Number(projectId));
if (!project) return null;

// useMemo for filtered/derived data
const filtered = useMemo(
  () => items.filter(i => i.name.includes(search)),
  [items, search]
);
```

## Imports

Path alias `@/` always ‚Äî never relative `../../..`.

Import order:
1. `react`
2. `next/...`, `next-intl`
3. Third-party (`@heroui/react`, `lucide-react`, `dayjs`...)
4. `@/types/...`
5. `@/hooks/...`
6. `@/utils/...`, `@/config/...`
7. `@/components/...`

Named imports from HeroUI ‚Äî never import `*`.

## File Naming

| Thing | Convention |
|---|---|
| Page (App Router) | `page.tsx`, `layout.tsx` |
| Client component | `PascalCase.tsx` |
| Utility / aggregate | `camelCase.ts` |
| Type file | `camelCase.ts`, singular noun |

## What Not to Add

- No `console.log` in committed code
- No `TODO` comments in JSX ‚Äî use GitHub issues
- No `as XType` casts to force invalid data through types
- No default exports for types or utilities ‚Äî named exports only
